emulate our toon with behind

00:04:23.186 --> 00:04:25.836
the wheel giggling, and show
titles like the world's

00:04:25.836 --> 00:04:27.996
fastest, most exclusive,
something or other.

00:04:27.996 --> 00:04:30.946
But Matt Farah's doing a great
job, a hell of a job, and

00:04:30.946 --> 00:04:31.806
everyone loves him.

00:04:31.806 --> 00:04:34.086
And he doesn't need a cartoon
image to be a--

00:04:34.086 --> 00:04:35.406
no, that's not fair.

00:04:35.406 --> 00:04:38.806
Anyway, despite the fact
McLaren's toon

00:04:38.806 --> 00:04:40.266
reminds me of Senninha.

00:04:40.266 --> 00:04:41.116
Remember?

00:04:41.116 --> 00:04:42.526
Created a generation ago.

00:04:42.526 --> 00:04:46.076
But what do you think about
cartoons, animations, movies,

00:04:46.076 --> 00:04:48.706
pushing the attraction
and appeal of racing?

00:04:48.706 --> 00:04:50.546
Remember this?

00:04:50.546 --> 00:04:52.456
Or even the Speed Racer movie.

00:04:52.456 --> 00:04:54.906
Or Cars, the movie.

00:04:54.906 --> 00:04:57.006
Or Michel Vaillant.

00:04:57.006 --> 00:04:58.796
So what do you think
about this type

00:04:58.796 --> 00:05:00.636
of marketing extension?

00:05:00.636 --> 00:05:03.396
Or is it better for McLaren to
market the more traditional

00:05:03.396 --> 00:05:06.786
